              <li>No credit will be given for this course unless both CLAS 230D1 and CLAS 230D2 are successfully completed in consecutive terms</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/clas-331" class="program-course-title">
              CLAS 331 Intermediate Modern Greek Language (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-20852" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Classics              : Competence in the language at the intermediate level through the study of grammar, vocabulary and derivatives. Excerpts in prose and poetry introducing the civilization of modern Greece.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Georgios Kellaris (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisite: CLAS 230 or CLAS 235 or CLAS 237 or permission of the instructor </li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/clas-332" class="program-course-title">
              CLAS 332 The Modern Greek Novel (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
